it would be such...

785
00:38:11.440 --> 00:38:13.160
- Ohh! You are naked!
- Huh?

786
00:38:13.520 --> 00:38:16.320
Oh. for sure. we're
a naturalist club.

787
00:38:16.560 --> 00:38:19.600
Yeah. In Zootropolis.
anyone can be anything.

788
00:38:19.840 --> 00:38:21.760
These guys. they be naked.

789
00:38:22.000 --> 00:38:24.880
Nangi's just on the other side
of the Pleasure Pool.

790
00:38:32.440 --> 00:38:33.520
Oh. boy.

791
00:38:33.520 --> 00:38:35.480
Does this make you uncomfortable?

792
00:38:35.680 --> 00:38:39.080
Because if so. there is no
shame in calling it quits.

793
00:38:39.320 --> 00:38:41.200
Yes. there is.

794
00:38:41.440 --> 00:38:43.360
Boy. that's the spirit.

795
00:38:44.640 --> 00:38:46.160
Yeah. some mammals say...

796
00:38:46.280 --> 00:38:47.680
the naturalist life is weird...

797
00:38:47.920 --> 00:38:49.840
but you know what I say is weird?

798
00:38:50.040 --> 00:38:51.920
Clothes on animals!

799
00:38:52.760 --> 00:38:54.360
- Here we go.
- Mmm...

800
00:38:54.680 --> 00:38:56.720
As you can see. Nangi's an elephant...

801
00:38:56.880 --> 00:38:59.200
so she'll totally remember everything.

802
00:38:59.440 --> 00:39:00.520
Hey. Nangi.

803
00:39:00.720 --> 00:39:02.400
These dudes have some questions...

804
00:39:02.520 --> 00:39:03.840
about Emmitt the otter.

805
00:39:03.960 --> 00:39:04.880
Who?

806
00:39:05.040 --> 00:39:06.760
Uh... Emmitt Otterton?

807
00:39:06.920 --> 00:39:08.400
Been coming to your
yoga class for like...

808
00:39:08.600 --> 00:39:09.760
6 years?

809
00:39:10.000 --> 00:39:11.520
I have no memory of this beaver.

810
00:39:11.720 --> 00:39:13.400
He's an otter. actually.

811
00:39:13.600 --> 00:39:15.280
He was here a couple
Wednesdays ago. remember?

812
00:39:15.440 --> 00:39:16.400
No.

813
00:39:16.520 --> 00:39:17.520
Yeah. he was wearing...

814
00:39:17.520 --> 00:39:20.080
a green cable-knit sweater vest...

815
00:39:20.320 --> 00:39:22.400
and a new pair of corduroy slacks.

816
00:39:22.560 --> 00:39:25.560
Oh. and a paisley tie.
sweet Windsor knot.

817
00:39:25.760 --> 00:39:27.600
Real tight. Remember that. Nangi?

818
00:39:27.960 --> 00:39:29.040
No.

819
00:39:29.560 --> 00:39:31.240
Yeah. and we both walked
him out. and he got into...

820
00:39:31.360 --> 00:39:33.920
this big old white car
with a silver trim.

821
00:39:34.160 --> 00:39:36.920
Needed a tune-up.
The third cylinder wasn't firing.

822
00:39:37.120 --> 00:39:39.080
- Remember that. Nangi?
- No.

823
00:39:39.560 --> 00:39:41.440
Uh...
You didn't happen to catch...

824
00:39:41.560 --> 00:39:43.880
the licence plate number. did you?

825
00:39:44.080 --> 00:39:46.920
Oh. for sure. It was 2-9...

826
00:39:47.160 --> 00:39:48.880
T-H-D...

827
00:39:49.080 --> 00:39:50.960
- 0-3.
0-3. Wow.

828
00:39:51.240 --> 00:39:52.600
This is a lot of great info. Thank you.

829
00:39:52.800 --> 00:39:55.920
Told you Nangi has a mind
like a steel trap.

830
00:39:56.160 --> 00:40:00.000
I wish I had a memory like an elephant.

831
00:40:01.400 --> 00:40:03.440
Well. I had a ball.

832
00:40:03.680 --> 00:40:04.960
You are welcome for the clue...

833
00:40:05.200 --> 00:40:07.160
and seeing as how any moron
can run a plate...

834
00:40:07.320 --> 00:40:10.120
I will take that pen and bid you <i>adieu.</i>

835
00:40:10.600 --> 00:40:13.080
The plate. I can't run a plate.

836
00:40:13.280 --> 00:40:14.560
I'm not in the system yet.

837
00:40:14.960 --> 00:40:16.680
Give me the pen. please.

838
00:40:16.920 --> 00:40:18.400
What was it you said?

839
00:40:18.640 --> 00:40:20.640
"Any moron can run a plate"?

840
00:40:20.840 --> 00:40:23.720
Gosh. If only there were
a moron around...

841
00:40:23.840 --> 00:40:25.440
who were up to the task.

842
00:40:25.640 --> 00:40:27.040
Rabbit. I did what you asked!

843
00:40:27.160 --> 00:40:28.800
You can't keep me on the hook forever.

844
00:40:29.000 --> 00:40:31.560
Not forever. Well. I only
have 36 hours left...

845
00:40:31.680 --> 00:40:33.320
to solve this case.

846
00:40:33.560 --> 00:40:35.880
So can you run the plate or not?

847
00:40:37.320 --> 00:40:39.560
Actually. I just remembered...

848
00:40:39.800 --> 00:40:41.160
<i>I have a pal at the DMV.</i>

849
00:40:42.720 --> 00:40:43.960
<i>Flash is the fastest guy in there.</i>

850
00:40:43.960 --> 00:40:45.640
If you need something done. he's on it.

851
00:40:45.840 --> 00:40:47.320
I hope so. We are
really fighting the clock...

852
00:40:47.480 --> 00:40:48.480
and every minute counts.

853
00:40:49.360 --> 00:40:53.400
Wait. They're all sloths?

854
00:41:21.680 --> 00:41:23.280
You said this was going to be quick!

855
00:41:23.520 --> 00:41:25.040
Are you saying
that because he's a sloth...

856
00:41:25.200 --> 00:41:26.480
he can't be fast?

857
00:41:26.680 --> 00:41:29.160
I thought in Zootropolis.
anyone could be anything.

858
00:41:29.560 --> 00:41:30.960
Flash. Flash. hundred-yard dash.

859
00:41:31.080 --> 00:41:32.160
Buddy. it's nice to see you.

860
00:41:33.560 --> 00:41:35.280
Nice to...

861
00:41:36.200 --> 00:41:37.280
see you...

862
00:41:38.760 --> 00:41:39.800
too.

863
00:41:40.040 --> 00:41:42.280
Hey. Flash. I'd love you
to meet my friend.

864
00:41:42.400 --> 00:41:43.960
Uh. darling. I've forgotten your name.

865
00:41:44.080 --> 00:41:45.080
Hmm.

866
00:41:45.200 --> 00:41:47.680
Officer Judy Hopps. ZPD. how are you?

867
00:41:47.880 --> 00:41:49.160
I am...

868
00:41:49.760 --> 00:41:50.800
doing...

869
00:41:51.400 --> 00:41:52.680
just...

870
00:41:53.040 --> 00:41:54.040
Fine?

871
00:41:54.240 --> 00:41:56.400
...as well as...

872
00:41:56.600 --> 00:41:57.720
I can...

873
00:41:58.240 --> 00:41:59.240
- be.
- Hmm.

874
00:41:59.240 --> 00:42:00.480
- What...
- Hang in there.

875
00:42:00.720 --> 00:42:01.760
...can I...

876
00:42:02.480 --> 00:42:03.840
- do...
- Well. I was hoping...

877
00:42:04.000 --> 00:42:05.160
- you could run a...
- ...for you...

878
00:42:05.400 --> 00:42:06.480
Well. I was hoping you could...

879
00:42:06.480 --> 00:42:07.560
...today?

880
00:42:10.400 --> 00:42:12.720
Well. I was hoping you could
run a plate for us.

881
00:42:12.960 --> 00:42:14.560
We are in a really big hurry.

882
00:42:16.320 --> 00:42:17.480
Sure.

883
00:42:17.760 --> 00:42:19.000
What's the...

884
00:42:19.600 --> 00:42:21.320
- plate...
- 2-9-T...

885
00:42:21.600 --> 00:42:22.640
...number?

886
00:42:23.600 --> 00:42:25.520
2-9-T-H-D-0-3

887
00:42:34.720 --> 00:42:35.720
Two...

888
00:42:38.080 --> 00:42:39.240
nine...

889
00:42:39.560 --> 00:42:41.520
T-H-D-0-3.

890
00:42:42.480 --> 00:42:43.600
...T...

891
00:42:44.440 --> 00:42:45.840
H-D-0-3.

892
00:42:46.760 --> 00:42:47.720
...H...

893
00:42:47.720 --> 00:42:49.720
D-0-3.

894
00:42:52.960 --> 00:42:54.040
- ...D...
- Mmm-hmm.

895
00:42:54.040 --> 00:42:55.520
0-3.

896
00:42:56.920 --> 00:42:57.880
...0...

897
00:42:57.880 --> 00:42:59.000
3.

898
00:43:01.000 --> 00:43:02.280
Hey. Flash. want to hear a joke?

899
00:43:02.480 --> 00:43:03.640
No!

900
00:43:04.120 --> 00:43:05.400
Sure.

901
00:43:05.600 --> 00:43:09.640
Okay. What do you call
a three-humped camel?

902
00:43:10.640 --> 00:43:12.000
I don't...

903
00:43:12.240 --> 00:43:13.400
know.

904
00:43:13.640 --> 00:43:14.720
What...

905
00:43:14.720 --> 00:43:15.800
do...

906
00:43:16.000 --> 00:43:17.600
you call...

907
00:43:17.800 --> 00:43:19.560
- a...
- Three-humped camel.

908
00:43:19.800 --> 00:43:21.320
...three-humped...

909
00:43:21.480 --> 00:43:22.400
camel?

910
00:43:23.480 --> 00:43:24.440
Pregnant.

911
00:43:40.000 --> 00:43:41.360
Ha-ha! Yes. very funny. very funny.

912
00:43:41.600 --> 00:43:42.800
Can we please just focus on the...

913
00:43:43.000 --> 00:43:44.280
- Hey...
- Wait. wait. wait!

914
00:43:44.480 --> 00:43:45.800
...Priscilla!

915
00:43:46.000 --> 00:43:47.160
Oh. no!

916
00:43:48.040 --> 00:43:49.640
Yes...

917
00:43:49.840 --> 00:43:51.360
Flash?

918
00:43:51.600 --> 00:43:52.480
- What...
- Oh!

919
00:43:52.480 --> 00:43:53.520
do...

920
00:43:53.680 --> 00:43:55.280
- No!
- ...you call a...

921
00:43:55.400 --> 00:43:56.640
A three-humped camel? "Pregnant!"

922
00:43:56.800 --> 00:43:57.720
Okay. great. we got it.

923
00:43:57.960 --> 00:44:00.280
- ...three... humped...
- Please just...

924
00:44:12.880 --> 00:44:14.440
Here...
- Yeah. Hurry.

925
00:44:14.680 --> 00:44:16.640
- ...you...
- Thank you. "2-9-T-H-D-0-3."

926
00:44:16.640 --> 00:44:17.760
...go.

927
00:44:18.040 --> 00:44:20.280
It's registered
to Tundratown Limo Service.

928
00:44:20.520 --> 00:44:22.520
A limo took Otterton.
and the limo's in Tundratown!

929
00:44:22.720 --> 00:44:23.720
It's in Tundratown!

930
00:44:23.880 --> 00:44:25.440
Way to hustle. bud.
I love you. I owe you.

931
00:44:25.720 --> 00:44:27.400
Hurry! We gotta beat
the rush hour. and...

932
00:44:27.680 --> 00:44:29.920
It's night?

933
00:44:30.320 --> 00:44:32.320
Closed. Great.

934
00:44:32.720 --> 00:44:33.600
Mmm.
And I will bet you...

935
00:44:33.840 --> 00:44:36.520
you don't have
a warrant to get in. Hmm?

936
00:44:36.720 --> 00:44:38.560
Darn it. It's a bummer.

937
00:44:38.800 --> 00:44:40.520
You wasted the day on purpose.

938
00:44:40.720 --> 00:44:42.640
Madam. I have a fake badge.

939
00:44:42.800 --> 00:44:44.880
I would never impede
your pretend investigation.

940
00:44:45.120 --> 00:44:47.880
It's not a pretend
investigation. Look. see?

941
00:44:48.080 --> 00:44:50.360
See him? This otter is missing.

942
00:44:50.880 --> 00:44:53.120
Well. then they should've
gotten a real cop to find him.

943
00:44:53.360 --> 00:44:54.560
What is your problem?

944
00:44:54.800 --> 00:44:56.800
Does seeing me fail somehow
make you feel better...

945
00:44:56.920 --> 00:44:58.560
about your own sad. miserable life?

946
00:44:58.840 --> 00:45:00.800
It does. 100%.

947
00:45:01.040 --> 00:45:04.160
Now. since you're sans warrant...

948
00:45:04.400 --> 00:45:07.160
I guess we're... done?

949
00:45:08.920 --> 00:45:11.920
Fine. We are done. Here's your pen.

950
00:45:13.200 --> 00:45:14.400
Hey!

951
00:45:17.840 --> 00:45:19.280
First off. you throw like a bunny.

952
00:45:19.560 --> 00:45:21.520
Second. you're a very sore loser.

953
00:45:21.680 --> 00:45:22.960
See you later. Officer Fluff.

954
00:45:23.200 --> 00:45:25.920
So sad this is over.
I wish I could've helped more.

955
00:45:26.200 --> 00:45:28.200
The thing is. you don't need a warrant...

956
00:45:28.360 --> 00:45:29.480
if you have probable cause...

957
00:45:29.480 --> 00:45:30.640
and I'm pretty sure I saw...

958
00:45:30.760 --> 00:45:33.440
a shifty lowlife climbing the fence.

959
00:45:33.680 --> 00:45:36.120
So you're helping plenty. Come on.

960
00:45:38.360 --> 00:45:41.000
2-9-T-H-D-0-3.
This is it!

961
00:45:49.960 --> 00:45:51.080
Polar bear fur.

962
00:45:54.280 --> 00:45:55.680
- Oh. my God!
- What? What?

963
00:45:56.080 --> 00:45:58.600
The Velvety Pipes of Jerry Vole.

964
00:45:58.920 --> 00:46:00.680
- But on CD.

965
00:46:00.920 --> 00:46:02.360
Who still uses CDs?

966
00:46:08.480 --> 00:46:10.840
Carrots. if your otter was here...

967
00:46:10.960 --> 00:46:12.720
he had a very bad day.

968
00:46:14.400 --> 00:46:16.680
Those are claw marks.

969
00:46:17.440 --> 00:46:19.040
You ever seen anything like this?

970
00:46:19.280 --> 00:46:20.320
No.

971
00:46:20.800 --> 00:46:22.240
Oh. wait. look.

972
00:46:24.400 --> 00:46:26.520
This is him.
Emmitt Otterton.

973
00:46:26.800 --> 00:46:29.080
He was definitely here.

974
00:46:29.320 --> 00:46:31.400
What do you think happened?

975
00:46:34.160 --> 00:46:35.320
Well. now.
wait a minute.

976
00:46:36.120 --> 00:46:40.040
Polar bear fur.
Rat Pack music. fancy cup?

977
00:46:40.320 --> 00:46:41.280
I know whose car this is. We got to go.

978
00:46:41.960 --> 00:46:43.040
Why? Whose car is it?

979
00:46:43.040 --> 00:46:44.600
The most feared crime-boss
in Tundratown.

980
00:46:44.760 --> 00:46:46.040
They call him Mr Big.

981
00:46:46.320 --> 00:46:48.600
And he does not like me.
So we gotta go!

982
00:46:48.840 --> 00:46:50.520
I'm not leaving. This is a crime scene.

983
00:46:50.680 --> 00:46:51.800
Well. it's gonna be
an even bigger crime scene...

984
00:46:51.960 --> 00:46:53.040
if Mr Big finds me here...

985
00:46:53.040 --> 00:46:54.640
so we're leaving right now.

986
00:46:56.360 --> 00:46:57.320
Raymond!

987
00:46:57.520 --> 00:46:59.920
And is that Kevin? Long time. no see.

988
00:47:00.160 --> 00:47:01.400
And. speaking of "no see"...

989
00:47:01.520 --> 00:47:04.720
how about you forget you saw me. huh?

990
00:47:05.000 --> 00:47:06.080
For old times' sake?

991
00:47:06.080 --> 00:47:07.200
That's a no.

992
00:47:17.520 --> 00:47:19.200
Oh...

993
00:47:21.200 --> 00:47:22.240
What did you do that made...

994
00:47:22.240 --> 00:47:23.560
Mr Big so mad at you?

995
00:47:23.840 --> 00:47:27.200
I. uh. I may have sold him
a very expensive wool rug...

996
00:47:27.400 --> 00:47:31.240
that was made from the fur of a skunk...

997
00:47:31.480 --> 00:47:33.400
...'s butt.

998
00:47:34.480 --> 00:47:36.720
Oh. sweet cheese and crackers.

999
00:47:51.520 --> 00:47:52.760
Is that Mr Big?

1000
00:47:53.000 --> 00:47:54.040
No.

1001
00:47:54.160 --> 00:47:55.240
What about him?

1002
00:47:55.520 --> 00:47:56.760
- Is that him?
- No!

1003
00:47:59.680 --> 00:48:00.760
That's got to be him.

1004
00:48:01.000 --> 00:48:02.480
Stop talking. stop talking. stop talking!

1005
00:48:11.040 --> 00:48:12.760
- Huh.
- Mr Big. sir.

1006
00:48:12.880 --> 00:48:13.920
This is a simple...

1007
00:48:15.560 --> 00:48:16.640
Yeah. Here...

1008
00:48:17.480 --> 00:48:18.640
Mmm...

1009
00:48:19.200 --> 00:48:20.800
This is a simple misunderstanding.

1010
00:48:21.000 --> 00:48:21.960
Oh...

1011
00:48:22.360 --> 00:48:23.600
You come here. unannounced...

1012
00:48:23.720 --> 00:48:25.480
on the day my daughter
is to be married.

1013
00:48:25.920 --> 00:48:26.800
Well. actually. we were brought here...

1014
00:48:27.000 --> 00:48:27.960
against our will. so...

1015
00:48:29.600 --> 00:48:31.880
The point is. I did not know
that it was your car...

1016
00:48:32.120 --> 00:48:34.560
and I certainly did not know
about your daughter's wedding.

1017
00:48:34.800 --> 00:48:35.800
Meh.

1018
00:48:35.920 --> 00:48:37.680
I trusted you. Nicky.

1019
00:48:37.920 --> 00:48:39.800
I welcomed you into my home.

1020
00:48:40.000 --> 00:48:42.120
We broke bread together.

1021
00:48:42.680 --> 00:48:44.640
Gram-mama made you a cannoli.

1022
00:48:44.880 --> 00:48:47.040
And how did you repay my generosity?

1023
00:48:47.280 --> 00:48:51.200
With a rug made from the butt
of a skunk.

1024
00:48:51.440 --> 00:48:53.120
A skunk-butt rug.

1025
00:48:53.400 --> 00:48:54.840
You disrespected me.

1026
00:48:55.120 --> 00:48:57.200
You disrespected my Gram-mama...

1027
00:48:57.360 --> 00:48:59.800
who I buried in that skunk butt rug.

1028
00:49:01.320 --> 00:49:03.840
I told you never to show
your face here again...

1029
00:49:04.040 --> 00:49:05.040
but here you are...

1030
00:49:05.280 --> 00:49:08.000
snooping around with this...

1031
00:49:08.240 --> 00:49:09.480
What are you? A performer?

1032
00:49:09.680 --> 00:49:10.840
What's with the costume?

1033
00:49:11.040 --> 00:49:12.000
Sir. I am a...

1034
00:49:12.120 --> 00:49:13.520
Mime! She is a mime.

1035
00:49:13.800 --> 00:49:15.720
This... mime cannot speak.

1036
00:49:15.880 --> 00:49:16.880
You can't speak if you're a mime.

1037
00:49:17.120 --> 00:49:18.480
- No. I am a cop.
- Ugh...

1038
00:49:18.680 --> 00:49:20.080
And I'm on the Emmitt Otterton case.

1039
00:49:20.320 --> 00:49:22.840
And my evidence puts him in your car.

1040
00:49:23.040 --> 00:49:24.520
So intimidate me all you want.

1041
00:49:24.760 --> 00:49:26.760
I'm going to find out
what you did to that otter...

1042
00:49:26.920 --> 00:49:29.440
if it's the last thing I do.

1043
00:49:30.240 --> 00:49:31.200
Meh.

1044
00:49:31.560 --> 00:49:34.360
Then I have only one request.

1045
00:49:34.600 --> 00:49:37.920
Say hello to Gram-mama. Ice 'em.

1046
00:49:38.080 --> 00:49:39.520
Whoa!

1047
00:49:39.640 --> 00:49:41.080
I didn't see nothing!
I'm not saying nothing!

1048
00:49:41.320 --> 00:49:42.440
And you never will.

1049
00:49:42.680 --> 00:49:44.240
- Please! No. no. no!
- Put me down!

1050
00:49:44.480 --> 00:49:46.680
If you're mad at me about
the rug. I've got more rugs!

1051
00:49:46.920 --> 00:49:50.960
Oh. Daddy! It's time for our dance!

1052
00:49:52.440 --> 00:49:53.560
Oh. what did we say?

1053
00:49:53.840 --> 00:49:55.920
No icing anyone at my wedding!

1054
00:49:56.160 --> 00:49:58.560
I have to. baby. Daddy has to.

1055
00:49:58.760 --> 00:49:59.720
- Ice 'em.

1056
00:49:59.840 --> 00:50:00.760
No. no. no!

1057
00:50:00.920 --> 00:50:01.880
Wait. Please!

1058
00:50:02.360 --> 00:50:05.200
She's the bunny
that saved my life yesterday!

1059
00:50:05.480 --> 00:50:06.760
From that giant donut.

1060
00:50:07.000 --> 00:50:07.920
This bunny?

1061
00:50:08.160 --> 00:50:09.800
Yeah! Hi!

1062
00:50:10.040 --> 00:50:12.400
Hi. I love your dress.

1063
00:50:12.640 --> 00:50:14.400
- Oh. Thank you.
Oh.

1064
00:50:14.680 --> 00:50:15.600
Put 'em down.

1065
00:50:19.360 --> 00:50:20.760
You've done me a great service.

1066
00:50:21.040 --> 00:50:23.120
I will help you find the otter.

1067
00:50:23.360 --> 00:50:28.240
I will take your kindness
and pay it forward.

1068
00:50:33.880 --> 00:50:35.400
Smile.

1069
00:50:36.040 --> 00:50:37.760
Hey. hey. hey. hey!

1070
00:50:39.840 --> 00:50:41.520
Hey. hey. hey. hey!

1071
00:50:46.720 --> 00:50:47.640
Hmm.

1072
00:50:56.280 --> 00:50:57.920
Otterton
is my florist.

1073
00:50:58.520 --> 00:51:00.760
He's like a part of the family.

1074
00:51:00.960 --> 00:51:03.920
He had something important
he wanted to discuss.

1075
00:51:04.200 --> 00:51:07.040
That's why I sent that car to pick him up.

1076
00:51:07.800 --> 00:51:09.480
But he never arrived.

1077
00:51:09.960 --> 00:51:11.280
Because he was attacked.

1078
00:51:11.520 --> 00:51:14.120
No. He attacked.

1079
00:51:14.640 --> 00:51:15.680
Otterton?

1080
00:51:15.960 --> 00:51:18.960
Otterton. He went crazy.

1081
00:51:19.200 --> 00:51:23.120
Ripped up the car. scared
my driver half to death...

1082
00:51:23.320 --> 00:51:25.680
and disappeared into the night.

1083
00:51:25.920 --> 00:51:29.040
But he's a sweet little otter.

1084
00:51:29.200 --> 00:51:34.320
Hmm. My child. we may
be evolved. but deep down...

1085
00:51:34.560 --> 00:51:36.800
we are still animals.

1086
00:51:38.960 --> 00:51:39.920
<i>You want to find Otterton.</i>

1087
00:51:39.920 --> 00:51:41.960
<i>talk to the driver of that car.</i>

1088
00:51:42.240 --> 00:51:43.640
<i>His name is Manchas...</i>

1089
00:51:43.840 --> 00:51:46.480
<i>lives in the Rainforest District.</i>

1090
00:51:46.680 --> 00:51:49.160
<i>Only he can tell you more.</i>

1091
00:51:53.000 --> 00:51:54.560
Mr Manchas?

1092
00:51:54.800 --> 00:51:56.720
Judy Hopps. ZPD.

1093
00:51:56.960 --> 00:52:00.000
We just wanna know what
happened to Emmitt Otterton.

1094
00:52:04.920 --> 00:52:05.920
You...

1095
00:52:06.160 --> 00:52:07.320
should be asking...

1096
00:52:08.320 --> 00:52:10.840
- what happened to me.
Whoa!

1097
00:52:11.360 --> 00:52:14.400
Uh. a teensy otter did that?

1098
00:52:14.640 --> 00:52:15.720
What happened?

1099
00:52:15.960 --> 00:52:18.000
He was an animal.

1100
00:52:19.360 --> 00:52:20.280
<i>Down...</i>

1101
00:52:20.640 --> 00:52:22.840
<i>on all fours.</i>

1102
00:52:25.920 --> 00:52:27.280
<i>He was a savage!</i>

1103
00:52:38.120 --> 00:52:39.240
There was no warning.

1104
00:52:39.480 --> 00:52:42.280
He just kept yelling about
the Night Howlers.

1105
00:52:42.520 --> 00:52:45.360
Over and over. The Night Howlers.

1106
00:52:45.600 --> 00:52:48.800
So you know about
the Night Howlers. too?

1107
00:52:49.040 --> 00:52:50.360
Good. Good. good.

1108
00:52:50.640 --> 00:52:52.200
Because the Night Howlers...

1109
00:52:52.320 --> 00:52:55.200
are exactly what we are here
to talk about.

1110
00:52:55.480 --> 00:52:56.760
- Right?
- Yup.

1111
00:52:57.640 --> 00:52:59.560
So. uh. so you just open the door...

1112
00:52:59.760 --> 00:53:01.320
and tell us what you know...

1113
00:53:01.560 --> 00:53:03.720
and we will tell you
what we know. Okay?

1114
00:53:05.440 --> 00:53:07.400
Okay.

1115
00:53:08.480 --> 00:53:10.400
Clever fox.

1116
00:53:14.160 --> 00:53:16.240
Mr Manchas?

1117
00:53:20.520 --> 00:53:21.440
Buddy?

1118
00:53:21.600 --> 00:53:22.560
Are you...

1119
00:53:22.800 --> 00:53:23.760
okay?

1120
00:53:26.680 --> 00:53:28.240
Run. Run!

1121
00:53:33.240 --> 00:53:34.280
What is wrong with him?

1122
00:53:34.560 --> 00:53:35.800
I don't know!

1123
00:53:40.840 --> 00:53:41.800
- Jump!

1124
00:53:44.480 --> 00:53:45.440
Come on!

1125
00:53:50.440 --> 00:53:52.960
- Head down!
- Oh. Oh!

1126
00:53:53.560 --> 00:53:54.800
Officer Hopps to Dispatch.

1127
00:53:55.080 --> 00:53:56.680
Are you familiar with Gazelle.
greatest singer

1128
00:53:56.880 --> 00:53:58.480
of our lifetime.
angel with horns?

1129
00:53:58.640 --> 00:54:00.280
- Okay. hold on. Keep watching.

1130
00:54:00.400 --> 00:54:01.520
Who's that beside her? Who is it?

1131
00:54:01.760 --> 00:54:05.040
<i>Wow. you are one hot dancer.
Benjamin Clawhauser.</i>

1132
00:54:06.760 --> 00:54:09.040
It's me! Did you think it was real?

1133
00:54:09.200 --> 00:54:10.120
It looks so real!

1134
00:54:10.360 --> 00:54:12.960
It's not. it's just a new app.
Hold on a second.

1135
00:54:13.200 --> 00:54:14.520
<i>Clawhauser!</i>

1136
00:54:14.760 --> 00:54:16.960
Clawhauser. listen to me.
we have a 10-91!

1137
00:54:17.080 --> 00:54:18.520
<i>Jaguar gone savage!</i>

1138
00:54:18.760 --> 00:54:19.720
Vine and Tuh-junja!

1139
00:54:19.960 --> 00:54:21.560
- It's "Tuh-hunga!"
- Whoa!

1140
00:54:21.720 --> 00:54:23.200
<i>Okay. we're
sending backup! Hopps?</i>

1141
00:54:23.760 --> 00:54:25.200
<i>Hopps!</i>

1142
00:54:26.760 --> 00:54:27.680
There!

1143
00:54:27.840 --> 00:54:29.240
Head for the sky trams!

1144
00:54:38.560 --> 00:54:40.160
Get in! Carrots.

1145
00:54:40.360 --> 00:54:41.320
- Carrots!

1146
00:54:41.480 --> 00:54:42.400
Go!

1147
00:54:43.800 --> 00:54:45.680
No. no. no!

1148
00:54:45.880 --> 00:54:47.080
Buddy.

1149
00:54:47.320 --> 00:54:49.160
- One predator to another...

1150
00:54:49.280 --> 00:54:50.400
No. no. no...

1151
00:54:53.280 --> 00:54:55.160
Now. I can tell you're a little tense...

1152
00:54:55.360 --> 00:54:56.920
so I'm just gonna give you
a little personal space! Ah!

1153
00:55:03.680 --> 00:55:05.600
Rabbit. whatever you do. do not let go!

1154
00:55:06.960 --> 00:55:08.600
- I'm gonna let go!
- No. you. what?

1155
00:55:08.840 --> 00:55:10.560
- One. two...
- No...

1156
00:55:10.720 --> 00:55:12.680
- I said. do not... Rabbit!

1157
00:55:17.800 --> 00:55:20.400
Carrots. You saved my life.

1158
00:55:20.640 --> 00:55:23.200
Well. That's what we do at the ZPD.

1159
00:55:38.880 --> 00:55:40.720
Hmm.

1160
00:55:40.920 --> 00:55:43.800
Well. this should be good.

1161
00:55:44.720 --> 00:55:46.040
I thought this was
just a missing mammal case...

1162
00:55:46.240 --> 00:55:47.720
but it's way bigger.

1163
00:55:47.920 --> 00:55:50.000
Mr Otterton did not just disappear.

1164
00:55:50.240 --> 00:55:54.240
I believe he and this jaguar.
they went savage. sir.

1165
00:55:54.440 --> 00:55:57.080
Savage? This isn't
the Stone Age. Hopps.

1166
00:55:57.200 --> 00:55:59.080
Animals don't "go savage."

1167
00:55:59.280 --> 00:56:02.400
I thought so. too. until I saw this.

1168
00:56:04.480 --> 00:56:07.120
What? He was right here.

1169
00:56:07.360 --> 00:56:08.920
The "savage" jaguar?

1170
00:56:09.400 --> 00:56:12.080
Sir. I know what I saw.
He almost killed us!

1171
00:56:12.960 --> 00:56:15.040
Or. maybe any aggressive predator...

1172
00:56:15.160 --> 00:56:17.400
looks savage to you rabbits.

1173
00:56:17.600 --> 00:56:18.600
Let's go!

1174
00:56:18.800 --> 00:56:19.760
Wait. sir.

1175
00:56:19.960 --> 00:56:21.640
I'm not the only one who saw him.

1176
00:56:21.880 --> 00:56:23.480
-  Nick!

1177
00:56:23.920 --> 00:56:25.800
You think I'm gonna believe a fox?

1178
00:56:26.040 --> 00:56:27.680
Well. he was a key witness. and I...

1179
00:56:27.920 --> 00:56:29.840
Two days to find the otter...

1180
00:56:30.080 --> 00:56:31.880
or you quit.

1181
00:56:32.080 --> 00:56:34.080
That was the deal.

1182
00:56:34.360 --> 00:56:35.920
Badge.

1183
00:56:40.960 --> 00:56:43.240
-  But. sir. we...
- Badge!

1184
00:56:48.800 --> 00:56:49.920
Uh. no.

1185
00:56:51.120 --> 00:56:52.560
What did you say. fox?

1186
00:56:52.800 --> 00:56:56.280
Sorry. What I said was. "no."

1187
00:56:56.560 --> 00:56:59.120
She will not be giving you that badge.

1188
00:56:59.320 --> 00:57:01.040
Look. you give her a clown vest...

1189
00:57:01.160 --> 00:57:03.040
and a three-wheeled joke-mobile...

1190
00:57:03.280 --> 00:57:04.480
and two days to solve a case...

1191
00:57:04.640 --> 00:57:06.200
you guys haven't cracked in two weeks?

1192
00:57:07.120 --> 00:57:08.120
Yeah.

1193
00:57:08.320 --> 00:57:09.800
It's no wonder she needed
to get help from a fox.

1194
00:57:10.040 --> 00:57:12.160
None of you guys
were gonna help her. were you?

1195
00:57:12.360 --> 00:57:13.480
- Ho...
- Here's the thing. Chief.

1196
00:57:13.680 --> 00:57:15.120
You gave her the 48 hours...

1197
00:57:15.360 --> 00:57:17.320
so. technically. we still have...

1198
00:57:17.560 --> 00:57:19.600
10 left to find our Mr Otterton...

1199
00:57:19.800 --> 00:57:22.000
and that is exactly what we're gonna do.

1200
00:57:22.200 --> 00:57:23.400
- So. if you'll excuse us...

1201
00:57:23.520 --> 00:57:26.640
we have a very big lead
to follow and a case to crack.

1202
00:57:26.800 --> 00:57:28.120
Good day.

1203
00:57:34.200 --> 00:57:35.480
Officer Hopps.

1204
00:57:58.000 --> 00:57:59.520
Thank you.

1205
00:58:00.680 --> 00:58:03.040
Never let them see that they get to you.

1206
00:58:04.360 --> 00:58:05.520
So...

1207
00:58:05.760 --> 00:58:08.120
things do get to you?

1208
00:58:08.360 --> 00:58:10.680
No. I mean. not any more...

1209
00:58:10.920 --> 00:58:12.480
but I was small...

1210
00:58:12.600 --> 00:58:14.880
and emotionally unbalanced
like you once.

1211
00:58:15.080 --> 00:58:16.120
Har-har.

1212
00:58:16.120 --> 00:58:18.120
No. it's true.

1213
00:58:18.360 --> 00:58:21.360
I think I was 8. or maybe 9...

1214
00:58:21.600 --> 00:58:23.520
and all I wanted to do...

1215
00:58:23.640 --> 00:58:26.840
was join the Junior Ranger Scouts.

1216
00:58:27.040 --> 00:58:29.480
<i>So. my mom scraped together
enough money...</i>

1217
00:58:29.600 --> 00:58:31.880
<i>to buy me a brand-new uniform...</i>

1218
00:58:32.080 --> 00:58:34.480
<i>because. by God. I was gonna fit in.</i>

1219
00:58:34.720 --> 00:58:37.960
<i>Even if I was the only
predator in the troop.</i>

1220
00:58:38.240 --> 00:58:39.200
<i>The only fox.</i>

1221
00:58:39.200 --> 00:58:40.320
Okay. Nick.

1222
00:58:40.320 --> 00:58:41.840
<i>I was gonna be
part of a pack.</i>

1223
00:58:42.080 --> 00:58:43.360
Ready for initiation?

1224
00:58:43.560 --> 00:58:45.400
Yeah. Pretty much born ready.

1225
00:58:46.080 --> 00:58:47.320
<i>I was so proud.</i>

1226
00:58:50.080 --> 00:58:51.080
Okay.

1227
00:58:51.240 --> 00:58:53.560
Now. raise your right paw
and deliver the oath.

1228
00:58:54.240 --> 00:58:57.240
I. Nicholas Wilde. promise to be brave...

1229
00:58:57.440 --> 00:59:00.320
loyal. helpful. and trustworthy.

1230
00:59:01.600 --> 00:59:04.320
Even though you're a fox?

1231
00:59:04.960 --> 00:59:06.080
What?

1232
00:59:09.120 --> 00:59:10.440
No. No! What did I do wrong. you guys?

1233
00:59:10.680 --> 00:59:12.760
No. please! Tell me!
What did I do wrong?

1234
00:59:12.960 --> 00:59:14.680
<i>What did I do?</i>

1235
00:59:14.800 --> 00:59:16.160
- No...

1236
00:59:16.520 --> 00:59:17.880
If you thought we would ever
trust a fox...

1237
00:59:17.880 --> 00:59:19.040
without a muzzle...

1238
00:59:19.600 --> 00:59:21.120
you're even dumber than you look!

1239
00:59:22.440 --> 00:59:23.520
Cry baby.

1240
00:59:23.520 --> 00:59:26.280
Aw. is he gonna cry?

1241
00:59:41.960 --> 00:59:44.480
<i>I learned
two things that day.</i>

1242
00:59:44.760 --> 00:59:45.960
<i>One...</i>

1243
00:59:46.160 --> 00:59:50.160
I was never gonna let anyone
see that they got to me.

1244
00:59:51.000 --> 00:59:53.280
And two?

1245
00:59:53.520 --> 00:59:56.080
If the world's only gonna see a fox...

1246
00:59:56.240 --> 00:59:58.600
as shifty and untrustworthy...

1247
00:59:58.800 --> 01:00:01.760
there's no point in trying
to be anything else.

1248
01:00:01.960 --> 01:00:05.480
Nick. you are so much more than that.

1249
01:00:09.680 --> 01:00:11.280
Boy. look at that traffic down there.

1250
01:00:11.480 --> 01:00:13.120
How about we go out to Chuck
in Traffic Central.

1251
01:00:13.320 --> 01:00:15.000
Chuck. how are things looking
on the Jam Cams?

1252
01:00:16.200 --> 01:00:18.280
Nick. I'm glad you told me.

1253
01:00:19.320 --> 01:00:20.760
The Jam Cams.

1254
01:00:21.000 --> 01:00:23.600
- Seriously. It's okay.
- No. no. no.

1255
01:00:23.840 --> 01:00:26.800
There are traffic cameras everywhere!

1256
01:00:27.000 --> 01:00:28.640
All over the canopy!

1257
01:00:28.840 --> 01:00:30.160
Whatever happened to that jaguar...

1258
01:00:30.400 --> 01:00:31.560
The traffic cams would have caught it!

1259
01:00:31.800 --> 01:00:33.000
- Bingo!
- Ho-ho!

1260
01:00:33.160 --> 01:00:34.440
Pretty sneaky. slick!

1261
01:00:34.680 --> 01:00:38.040
However. if you didn't have
access to the system before...

1262
01:00:38.320 --> 01:00:41.720
I doubt Chief Buffalo Butt
is gonna let you into it now.

1263
01:00:41.960 --> 01:00:43.200
No.

1264
01:00:44.000 --> 01:00:46.440
But I have a friend
at City Hall who might.

1265
01:00:47.320 --> 01:00:49.920
Sir. if we could just review
these very important...

1266
01:00:50.400 --> 01:00:51.400
- Sir...

1267
01:00:51.520 --> 01:00:52.720
I'm so sorry. Sir!

1268
01:00:53.000 --> 01:00:56.040
Okay. I heard you. Bellwether.
Just take care of it.

1269
01:00:56.720 --> 01:00:59.080
Please. And clear
my afternoon. I'm going out.

1270
01:00:59.320 --> 01:01:00.560
No. no! But. sir.
you do have a meeting...

1271
01:01:00.720 --> 01:01:01.800
with Herds and Grazing.

1272
01:01:01.800 --> 01:01:03.200
Sir. if I could just...

1273
01:01:05.000 --> 01:01:06.840
Oh. mutton chops.

1274
01:01:08.720 --> 01:01:10.080
Assistant Mayor Bellwether?

1275
01:01:10.320 --> 01:01:11.440
We need your help.

1276
01:01:13.040 --> 01:01:14.680
We just need to get into
the traffic cam database.

1277
01:01:23.840 --> 01:01:25.280
So fluffy!

1278
01:01:25.400 --> 01:01:26.440
Hey!

1279
01:01:26.440 --> 01:01:27.880
Sheep never let me get this close.

1280
01:01:28.120 --> 01:01:29.440
You can't just touch a sheep's wool!

1281
01:01:29.680 --> 01:01:30.760
It's like cotton candy.

1282
01:01:30.760 --> 01:01:31.840
Stop it!

1283
01:01:31.840 --> 01:01:33.000
Where to?

1284
01:01:33.520 --> 01:01:36.320
Uh. Rainforest District.
Vine and Tujunga.

1285
01:01:36.680 --> 01:01:38.480
There!
Traffic cams for the whole city.

1286
01:01:38.720 --> 01:01:40.880
Oh. this is so exciting.
actually!

1287
01:01:41.080 --> 01:01:42.640
I never get to do
anything this important.

1288
01:01:42.920 --> 01:01:45.200
But you're the Assistant Mayor
of Zootropolis.

1289
01:01:45.400 --> 01:01:47.760
Oh. I'm more of a glorified secretary.

1290
01:01:47.960 --> 01:01:50.360
I think Mayor Lionheart
just wanted the sheep vote.

1291
01:01:50.600 --> 01:01:51.760
But he did give me that nice mug.

1292
01:01:52.560 --> 01:01:53.800
Oh.
Hmm.

1293
01:01:54.040 --> 01:01:55.520
- Feels good to be appreciated.

1294
01:01:55.760 --> 01:01:56.960
<i>Smell-wether!</i>

1295
01:01:57.200 --> 01:01:59.840
Ugh. That's a fun little name
he likes to use.

1296
01:02:00.080 --> 01:02:01.880
I called him Lion-fart once.

1297
01:02:02.080 --> 01:02:03.280
He did not care for that.
Let me tell you...

1298
01:02:03.440 --> 01:02:04.480
it was not a good day for me.

1299
01:02:04.600 --> 01:02:05.640
Yes. sir?

1300
01:02:05.640 --> 01:02:07.040
<i>I thought you were going
to cancel my afternoon!</i>

1301
01:02:07.440 --> 01:02:09.200
Oh. dear. I better go.

1302
01:02:09.440 --> 01:02:10.880
Let me know what you find.

1303
01:02:11.080 --> 01:02:12.960
It was really nice for me to be...

1304
01:02:13.240 --> 01:02:14.240
<i>- While we're young...</i>
- Oh...

1305
01:02:14.240 --> 01:02:16.160
<i>- Smell-wether!</i>

1306
01:02:17.440 --> 01:02:19.200
You think when she goes
to sleep she counts herself?

1307
01:02:19.440 --> 01:02:21.120
Oh. shush. Okay. traffic cams.

1308
01:02:21.480 --> 01:02:24.480
Tujunga. Tujunga... We're in.

1309
01:02:30.200 --> 01:02:32.720
- Who are these guys?
Ugh.

1310
01:02:33.040 --> 01:02:35.920
Timberwolves.
Look at these dumb-dumbs.

1311
01:02:40.600 --> 01:02:43.120
Bet you a nickel
one of them is gonna howl.

1312
01:02:43.400 --> 01:02:44.520
- And there it is.

1313
01:02:44.760 --> 01:02:47.480
What is it with wolves
and the howling? It's like...

1314
01:02:47.720 --> 01:02:49.560
Howlers. Night Howlers.

1315
01:02:49.800 --> 01:02:51.880
That's what Manchas
was afraid of! Wolves!

1316
01:02:52.160 --> 01:02:53.400
The wolves are the Night Howlers.

1317
01:02:53.560 --> 01:02:54.680
If they took Manchas...

1318
01:02:54.680 --> 01:02:56.400
I'll bet they took Otterton. too.

1319
01:02:56.640 --> 01:02:59.120
All we gotta do is find out
where they went.

1320
01:03:06.640 --> 01:03:07.720
Wait. where did they go?

1321
01:03:07.720 --> 01:03:09.600
You know. if I wanted
to avoid surveillance...

1322
01:03:09.760 --> 01:03:10.920
because I was doing
something illegal...

1323
01:03:11.160 --> 01:03:12.200
which I never have...

1324
01:03:12.200 --> 01:03:14.000
I would use the maintenance tunnel 6B.

1325
01:03:14.800 --> 01:03:15.920
Which would put them out...

1326
01:03:16.520 --> 01:03:18.120
right there.

1327
01:03:18.600 --> 01:03:21.800
Well. look at you. Junior Detective.

1328
01:03:22.000 --> 01:03:24.080
You know. I think you'd actually...

1329
01:03:24.240 --> 01:03:26.160
make a pretty good cop.

1330
01:03:26.440 --> 01:03:28.160
- Ugh. How dare you.

1331
01:03:28.440 --> 01:03:29.560
Acacia Alley?

1332
01:03:29.800 --> 01:03:30.920
Ficus Underpass.

1333
01:03:31.200 --> 01:03:32.360
- South Canyon.
Mmm-hmm.

1334
01:03:32.600 --> 01:03:33.680
They're heading out of town.

1335
01:03:34.320 --> 01:03:35.720
Where does that road go?

1336
01:04:20.480 --> 01:04:21.520
Gary. quit it!

1337
01:04:21.640 --> 01:04:22.760
You're gonna start a howl.

1338
01:04:22.880 --> 01:04:24.080
- I didn't start it!

1339
01:04:31.520 --> 01:04:32.720
Come on.

1340
01:04:40.600 --> 01:04:43.120
You are a clever bunny.

1341
01:04:58.960 --> 01:05:02.080
It looks like
this was a hospital.

1342
01:05:15.200 --> 01:05:16.800
You know. after you. You're the cop.

1343
01:05:16.960 --> 01:05:17.880
Hmm.

1344
01:05:25.600 --> 01:05:28.000
-  Okay. all clear.
- Ugh.

1345
01:05:31.400 --> 01:05:32.400
Huh.

1346
01:05:32.720 --> 01:05:35.000
All this equipment is brand new.

1347
01:05:36.680 --> 01:05:37.680
Carrots.

1348
01:05:40.360 --> 01:05:41.400
Claw marks.

1349
01:05:41.520 --> 01:05:44.080
Yeah. huge. huge claw marks.
I mean. what kind of...

1350
01:06:03.680 --> 01:06:05.520
Mr Manchas.

1351
01:06:15.400 --> 01:06:16.600
It's him.

1352
01:06:16.960 --> 01:06:19.040
We found our otter.

1353
01:06:19.280 --> 01:06:20.680
Mr Otterton.

1354
01:06:20.920 --> 01:06:24.200
My name is Officer Judy Hopps.
Your wife sent me to find you.

1355
01:06:24.440 --> 01:06:25.600
We're gonna get you out of here now.

1356
01:06:27.520 --> 01:06:28.800
Or not.

1357
01:06:29.040 --> 01:06:31.240
Guess he's in no rush
to get home to the missus.

1358
01:06:31.680 --> 01:06:33.560
11. 12. 13. 14...

1359
01:06:33.840 --> 01:06:36.800
Not including Manchas. it's 14.

1360
01:06:37.040 --> 01:06:39.840
Chief Bogo handed out
14 missing mammal files.

1361
01:06:39.960 --> 01:06:41.000
They're all here.

1362
01:06:41.520 --> 01:06:43.960
All the missing mammals are right here.

1363
01:06:50.160 --> 01:06:52.840
Enough!
I don't want excuses. Doctor!

1364
01:06:53.040 --> 01:06:54.120
I want answers.

1365
01:06:54.240 --> 01:06:55.440
Mayor Lionheart. please.

1366
01:06:55.680 --> 01:06:57.320
We're doing everything we can.

1367
01:06:57.560 --> 01:06:58.560
Really?

1368
01:06:59.200 --> 01:07:00.440
Because I got a dozen
and a half animals here...

1369
01:07:00.560 --> 01:07:02.200
who have gone off-the-rails crazy...

1370
01:07:02.400 --> 01:07:03.840
and you can't tell me why.

1371
01:07:04.080 --> 01:07:06.760
Now. I'd call that awfully far
from "doing everything."

1372
01:07:07.040 --> 01:07:08.040
Sir...

1373
01:07:08.240 --> 01:07:10.040
it may be time to consider their biology.

1374
01:07:10.240 --> 01:07:12.080
What? What do you mean "biology?"

1375
01:07:12.240 --> 01:07:14.920
The only animals
going savage are predators.

1376
01:07:15.160 --> 01:07:17.880
We cannot keep it a secret.
We need to come forward.

1377
01:07:18.560 --> 01:07:20.880
Hmm. Great idea. Tell the public.

1378
01:07:21.080 --> 01:07:22.240
And how do you think they're...

1379
01:07:22.400 --> 01:07:24.000
gonna feel about their mayor...

1380
01:07:24.240 --> 01:07:25.840
who is a lion?

1381
01:07:26.080 --> 01:07:27.160
I'll be ruined!

1382
01:07:27.160 --> 01:07:28.480
Well.
what does Chief Bogo say?

1383
01:07:28.720 --> 01:07:30.760
Chief Bogo doesn't know.

1384
01:07:31.000 --> 01:07:33.800
And we are going to keep it that way.

1385
01:07:33.920 --> 01:07:35.840
- Oh. no. no. no!

1386
01:07:36.080 --> 01:07:37.120
Someone's here.

1387
01:07:37.400 --> 01:07:38.840
Sir. you need to go. now!

1388
01:07:39.120 --> 01:07:40.680
Security! Sweep the area!

1389
01:07:48.760 --> 01:07:50.440
Great! We're dead. We're dead.

1390
01:07:50.680 --> 01:07:53.080
That's it. I'm dead.
you're dead. Everybody's dead!

1391
01:07:53.280 --> 01:07:54.320
Can you swim?

1392
01:07:54.560 --> 01:07:57.240
What? Can I swim?
Yes. I can swim. Why?

1393
01:08:08.640 --> 01:08:10.040
No. no. no!

1394
01:08:17.320 --> 01:08:21.200
- Carrots! Hopps! Judy!

1395
01:08:21.920 --> 01:08:23.520
We gotta tell Bogo!

1396
01:08:23.640 --> 01:08:25.160
<i>Wow!</i>

1397
01:08:25.320 --> 01:08:29.160
<i>You are one hot dancer. Chief Bogo.</i>

1398
01:08:31.560 --> 01:08:33.320
- Chief Bogo!
- Not now!

1399
01:08:33.560 --> 01:08:35.560
- Wait. is that Gazelle?
- No.

1400
01:08:35.760 --> 01:08:38.440
<i>I'm Gazelle.
and you are one hot dancer.</i>

1401
01:08:38.640 --> 01:08:41.440
You have the app too? Oh...

1402
01:08:41.760 --> 01:08:42.880
Chief!

1403
01:08:43.120 --> 01:08:44.320
Clawhauser. can't you see
I'm working...

1404
01:08:44.480 --> 01:08:45.720
on the missing mammal cases?

1405
01:08:45.960 --> 01:08:47.960
Oh. oh. oh! Yes of course!
About that. sir.

1406
01:08:48.360 --> 01:08:49.440
Officer Hopps just called.

1407
01:08:49.680 --> 01:08:50.680
She found all of them.

1408
01:08:51.520 --> 01:08:53.520
<i>Wow! I'm impressed.</i>

1409
01:08:56.600 --> 01:08:57.840
Mayor Lionheart.
you have the right...

1410
01:08:58.000 --> 01:08:59.200
to remain silent. Anything...

1411
01:08:59.480 --> 01:09:02.000
You don't understand.
I was trying to protect the city!

1412
01:09:02.280 --> 01:09:04.280
You were just trying to protect your job.

1413
01:09:04.520 --> 01:09:07.400
No. Listen. we still don't know
why this is happening.

1414
01:09:07.640 --> 01:09:09.560
It could destroy Zootropolis.

1415
01:09:09.920 --> 01:09:11.120
You have the right to remain silent.

1416
01:09:11.360 --> 01:09:12.480
Anything you say can and will...

1417
01:09:12.640 --> 01:09:13.720
be used against you in a court of law.

1418
01:09:14.200 --> 01:09:17.360
You have the right...

1419
01:09:19.320 --> 01:09:20.480
<i>Ladies
and gentlemammals.</i>

1420
01:09:21.680 --> 01:09:23.320
<i>14 mammals went missing...</i>

1421
01:09:23.720 --> 01:09:27.280
<i>and all 14 have been found
by our newest recruit...</i>

1422
01:09:27.520 --> 01:09:28.760
<i>who will speak to you in a moment.</i>

1423
01:09:29.120 --> 01:09:30.120
<i>But first. let me remind you...</i>

1424
01:09:30.360 --> 01:09:31.360
Ugh. I'm so nervous.

1425
01:09:31.640 --> 01:09:33.360
Okay. Press Conference 101.

1426
01:09:33.560 --> 01:09:34.640
You wanna look smart?

1427
01:09:34.800 --> 01:09:36.040
Answer their question
with your own question...

1428
01:09:36.320 --> 01:09:39.280
and then answer that question.
Like this.

1429
01:09:39.520 --> 01:09:40.840
"Excuse me. Officer Hopps...

1430
01:09:41.000 --> 01:09:42.760
"uh. what can you tell us
about the case?"

1431
01:09:43.000 --> 01:09:44.520
"Well. was this a tough case?

1432
01:09:44.720 --> 01:09:46.680
"Yes. Yes. it was." You see?

1433
01:09:46.880 --> 01:09:48.640
You should be there with me.

1434
01:09:48.880 --> 01:09:50.160
We did this together.

1435
01:09:50.400 --> 01:09:53.440
Well. am I a cop? No. No. I am not.

1436
01:09:53.560 --> 01:09:55.720
Hmm. Funny you should say that...

1437
01:09:55.920 --> 01:09:58.200
because I've been thinking...

1438
01:09:58.480 --> 01:10:02.920
It would be nice to have a partner.

1439
01:10:07.520 --> 01:10:10.480
Here. In case you need
something to write with.

1440
01:10:13.080 --> 01:10:14.320
<i>At twenty-two hundred hours...</i>

1441
01:10:14.520 --> 01:10:15.960
<i>we found all these missing animals...</i>

1442
01:10:16.200 --> 01:10:18.600
Officer Hopps. it's time.

1443
01:10:18.840 --> 01:10:20.120
<i>They appear to be
in good health. physically...</i>

1444
01:10:20.240 --> 01:10:21.560
<i>- ...if not emotionally.</i>

1445
01:10:22.600 --> 01:10:24.680
So now. I'll turn things over...

1446
01:10:24.840 --> 01:10:27.600
to the officer who cracked the case.

1447
01:10:27.880 --> 01:10:29.520
- Officer Judy Hopps.

1448
01:10:31.240 --> 01:10:32.960
- Officer Hopps!
- Officer Hopps!

1449
01:10:33.200 --> 01:10:34.200
Over here!

1450
01:10:34.200 --> 01:10:35.240
Yes?

1451
01:10:35.400 --> 01:10:36.960
What can you tell us about
the animals that went savage?

1452
01:10:37.200 --> 01:10:41.760
Well. the animals
in question. um...

1453
01:10:44.800 --> 01:10:46.920
Are they all different species?

1454
01:10:47.120 --> 01:10:49.040
Yes. Yes. they are.

1455
01:10:50.640 --> 01:10:52.480
Okay.
so what is the connection?

1456
01:10:52.720 --> 01:10:54.680
Oh. all we know is that they...

1457
01:10:54.800 --> 01:10:56.400
are all members of the predator family.

1458
01:10:56.920 --> 01:10:59.600
So. predators are
the only ones going savage?

1459
01:11:00.120 --> 01:11:02.360
That is ac... Yes. that is accurate. Yes.

1460
01:11:02.600 --> 01:11:03.840
- Why? Why is this happening?

1461
01:11:04.080 --> 01:11:05.200
We still don't know.

1462
01:11:08.160 --> 01:11:11.760
It may have something
to do with biology.

1463
01:11:12.000 --> 01:11:13.200
What do you mean by that?

1464
01:11:13.440 --> 01:11:15.360
A biological component.

1465
01:11:15.600 --> 01:11:18.920
You know. something in their DNA.

1466
01:11:19.640 --> 01:11:22.000
In their DNA? Can you
elaborate on that. please?

1467
01:11:22.240 --> 01:11:26.080
Yes. what I mean is.
thousands of years ago...

1468
01:11:27.160 --> 01:11:32.280
uh. predators survived through
their aggressive...

1469
01:11:32.480 --> 01:11:34.160
hunting instincts.

1470
01:11:34.280 --> 01:11:35.320
For whatever reason...

1471
01:11:35.840 --> 01:11:37.680
they seem to be reverting back...

1472
01:11:38.280 --> 01:11:39.720
to their primitive. savage ways.

1473
01:11:39.720 --> 01:11:40.760
Of course they did.

1474
01:11:42.160 --> 01:11:44.000
<i>Aw. is he gonna cry?</i>

1475
01:11:44.240 --> 01:11:46.080
Officer Hopps. could it happen again?

1476
01:11:46.440 --> 01:11:49.120
It is possible. So we must be vigilant.

1477
01:11:49.360 --> 01:11:52.920
And we at the ZPD are prepared
and are here to protect you.

1478
01:11:53.200 --> 01:11:54.360
Will more mammals go savage?

1479
01:11:54.600 --> 01:11:55.720
What is being done to protect us?

1480
01:11:55.920 --> 01:11:57.120
Have you considered

1481
01:11:57.280 --> 01:11:58.360
a mandatory quarantine on predators?

1482
01:11:58.520 --> 01:12:00.120
Okay. thank you. Officer Hopps.

1483
01:12:00.280 --> 01:12:01.720
Uh. that's all the time that we have.

1484
01:12:02.000 --> 01:12:03.120
No more questions.

1485
01:12:05.840 --> 01:12:06.960
Was I okay?

1486
01:12:06.960 --> 01:12:09.200
Oh. you did fine.

1487
01:12:09.840 --> 01:12:11.080
Oh. that went so fast.

1488
01:12:11.080 --> 01:12:12.360
I didn't get a chance to mention you...

1489
01:12:12.560 --> 01:12:13.600
or say anything about how we...

1490
01:12:13.840 --> 01:12:16.240
Oh. I think you said plenty.

1491
01:12:16.800 --> 01:12:17.920
What do you mean?

1492
01:12:18.160 --> 01:12:20.600
"Clearly there's
a biological component?"

1493
01:12:20.840 --> 01:12:23.400
"These predators may be
reverting back...

1494
01:12:23.560 --> 01:12:25.600
"to their primitive. savage ways?"

1495
01:12:25.840 --> 01:12:27.400
Are you serious?

1496
01:12:27.680 --> 01:12:30.040
I just stated the facts of the case.

1497
01:12:30.320 --> 01:12:32.560
I mean. it's not like
a bunny could go savage.

1498
01:12:32.800 --> 01:12:34.600
Right. But a fox could. huh?

1499
01:12:34.840 --> 01:12:37.160
Nick. stop it. You're not like them.

1500
01:12:37.400 --> 01:12:39.200
Oh. there's a "them" now?

1501
01:12:39.400 --> 01:12:40.440
Ugh. You know what I mean.

1502
01:12:40.560 --> 01:12:42.040
You're not that kind of predator.

1503
01:12:42.240 --> 01:12:43.640
The kind that needs to be muzzled?

1504
01:12:43.920 --> 01:12:45.160
The kind that makes you think...

1505
01:12:45.320 --> 01:12:47.840
you need to carry around fox repellent?

1506
01:12:48.080 --> 01:12:49.080
Yeah. don't think I didn't...

1507
01:12:49.080 --> 01:12:51.720
notice that little item
the first time we met.

1508
01:12:51.920 --> 01:12:55.120
So let me ask you a question.
Are you afraid of me?

1509
01:12:56.760 --> 01:12:59.080
Do you think I might go nuts?

1510
01:12:59.720 --> 01:13:01.440
Do you think I might go savage?

1511
01:13:01.680 --> 01:13:03.720
Do you think I might try to...

1512
01:13:03.720 --> 01:13:04.840
eat you?

1513
01:13:08.600 --> 01:13:10.040
I knew it.

1514
01:13:12.360 --> 01:13:14.640
Just when I thought somebody
actually believed in me. huh.

1515
01:13:14.880 --> 01:13:18.560
Probably best if you don't
have a predator as a partner.

1516
01:13:24.360 --> 01:13:26.480
- No. Nick. Nick!

1517
01:13:26.720 --> 01:13:28.600
Officer Hopps! Were you just
threatened by that predator?

1518
01:13:28.840 --> 01:13:30.440
No. he's my friend.

1519
01:13:30.640 --> 01:13:32.440
We can't even trust our own friends?

1520
01:13:32.640 --> 01:13:34.320
That is not what I said! Please!

1521
01:13:34.480 --> 01:13:35.400
Are we safe?

1522
01:13:35.600 --> 01:13:37.200
Have any of our foxes gone savage?

1523
01:13:37.680 --> 01:13:39.960
{\an8}<i>More bad news
in this city gripped by fear.</i>

1524
01:13:40.160 --> 01:13:42.000
{\an8}<i>A caribou is in critical condition...</i>

1525
01:13:42.000 --> 01:13:43.240
{\an8}<i>the victim of a mauling...</i>

1526
01:13:43.360 --> 01:13:45.240
{\an8}<i>by a savage polar bear.</i>

1527
01:13:45.480 --> 01:13:47.920
{\an8}<i>This. the 27th such attack.
comes just one week...</i>

1528
01:13:48.120 --> 01:13:51.360
{\an8}<i>after ZPD Officer Judy Hopps
connected the violence...</i>

1529
01:13:51.480 --> 01:13:54.200
{\an8}<i>to traditionally predatory animals.</i>

1530
01:13:54.480 --> 01:13:56.240
{\an8}<i>Meanwhile. a peace rally organised...</i>

1531
01:13:56.360 --> 01:13:57.920
{\an8}<i>-by pop star Gazelle...</i>

1532
01:13:58.160 --> 01:13:59.480
{\an8}<i>was marred by protest.</i>

1533
01:13:59.680 --> 01:14:01.560
{\an8}<i>Go back to the forest. predator!</i>

1534
01:14:01.800 --> 01:14:03.280
{\an8}<i>I'm from the savanna!</i>

1535
01:14:03.480 --> 01:14:05.320
{\an8}<i>Zootropolis is a unique place.</i>

1536
01:14:05.520 --> 01:14:08.960
{\an8}<i>It's a crazy. beautiful. diverse city...</i>

1537
01:14:09.160 --> 01:14:11.480
{\an8}<i>where we celebrate our differences.</i>

1538
01:14:11.680 --> 01:14:13.040
{\an8}<i>This is not the Zootropolis I know.</i>

1539
01:14:14.640 --> 01:14:17.720
<i>The Zootropolis I know
is better than this.</i>

1540
01:14:17.960 --> 01:14:20.080
<i>We don't just blindly assign blame.</i>

1541
01:14:25.360 --> 01:14:27.480
<i>We don't know why these
attacks keep happening...</i>

1542
01:14:28.520 --> 01:14:30.240
<i>but it is irresponsible...</i>

1543
01:14:30.240 --> 01:14:32.560
<i>to label all predators as savages.</i>

1544
01:14:39.040 --> 01:14:41.080
That's not my Emmitt.

1545
01:14:43.560 --> 01:14:46.000
<i>We cannot
let fear divide us.</i>

1546
01:14:46.200 --> 01:14:50.680
<i>Please give me back
the Zootropolis I love.</i>

1547
01:14:53.920 --> 01:14:55.240
Come on. Hopps.

1548
01:14:55.480 --> 01:14:56.640
The new mayor wants to see us.

1549
01:14:56.880 --> 01:14:59.200
The mayor? Why?

1550
01:14:59.680 --> 01:15:02.320
It would seem you've arrived.

1551
01:15:05.680 --> 01:15:07.040
Clawhauser?

1552
01:15:07.280 --> 01:15:08.880
What are you doing?

1553
01:15:09.160 --> 01:15:10.240
Um...

1554
01:15:10.840 --> 01:15:12.640
They thought it would be better...

1555
01:15:12.880 --> 01:15:15.040
if a predator such as myself...

1556
01:15:15.240 --> 01:15:17.560
wasn't the first face that you see...

1557
01:15:17.760 --> 01:15:19.880
when you walk into the ZPD.

1558
01:15:20.160 --> 01:15:21.600
What?

1559
01:15:22.280 --> 01:15:23.760
They're gonna move me to records.

1560
01:15:23.760 --> 01:15:24.880
It's downstairs.

1561
01:15:25.560 --> 01:15:27.400
It's by the boiler.

1562
01:15:29.600 --> 01:15:31.080
Hopps!

1563
01:15:36.760 --> 01:15:39.400
Um. I don't understand.

1564
01:15:39.680 --> 01:15:42.600
Our city is 90% prey. Judy...

1565
01:15:42.840 --> 01:15:45.240
and right now
they're just really scared.

1566
01:15:46.040 --> 01:15:48.920
You're a hero to them. They trust you.

1567
01:15:49.120 --> 01:15:52.080
And so that's why Chief Bogo and I...

1568
01:15:52.200 --> 01:15:55.440
want you to be
the public face of the ZPD.

1569
01:16:00.240 --> 01:16:02.920
I'm... not...

1570
01:16:04.000 --> 01:16:05.600
I'm not a hero.

1571
01:16:06.440 --> 01:16:09.840
I came here to make
the world a better place...

1572
01:16:10.080 --> 01:16:11.520
but I think I broke it.

1573
01:16:11.760 --> 01:16:15.680
Don't give yourself
so much credit. Hopps.

1574
01:16:15.960 --> 01:16:17.280
The world has always been broken...

1575
01:16:17.440 --> 01:16:19.440
that's why we need good cops.

1576
01:16:21.040 --> 01:16:22.120
Like you.

1577
01:16:23.800 --> 01:16:28.680
With all due respect. sir. a good cop...

1578
01:16:28.960 --> 01:16:32.120
is supposed to serve and protect.

1579
01:16:32.400 --> 01:16:34.480
Help the city.

1580
01:16:34.840 --> 01:16:37.200
Not tear it apart.

1581
01:16:40.760 --> 01:16:42.920
I don't deserve this badge.

1582
01:16:43.040 --> 01:16:44.160
Hopps...

1583
01:16:44.360 --> 01:16:47.400
Judy. you've worked
so hard to get here.

1584
01:16:47.640 --> 01:16:50.040
It's what you wanted
since you were a kid.

1585
01:16:50.280 --> 01:16:52.000
You can't quit.

1586
01:16:52.240 --> 01:16:54.160
Thank you for the opportunity.

1587
01:17:13.720 --> 01:17:15.080
A dozen carrots.

1588
01:17:15.360 --> 01:17:16.400
- Thanks.
- Have a nice day.

1589
01:17:16.640 --> 01:17:17.640
Come on.

1590
01:17:24.080 --> 01:17:26.200
Hey. there. Jude. Jude the dude.

1591
01:17:26.360 --> 01:17:29.200
Remember that one?
How we doing?

1592
01:17:29.400 --> 01:17:30.480
I'm fine.

1593
01:17:30.480 --> 01:17:32.960
You are not fine. Your ears are droopy.

1594
01:17:33.360 --> 01:17:36.440
Why did I think
I could make a difference?

1595
01:17:36.680 --> 01:17:38.360
Because you're a trier. that's why.

1596
01:17:38.600 --> 01:17:40.200
You've always been a trier.

1597
01:17:40.400 --> 01:17:41.600
Oh. I tried.

1598
01:17:41.880 --> 01:17:43.880
And it made life so much worse...

1599
01:17:44.040 --> 01:17:45.760
for so many innocent predators.

1600
01:17:46.040 --> 01:17:47.040
- Oh. not all of them. though.

1601
01:17:47.160 --> 01:17:48.240
Speak of the devil.

1602
01:17:48.360 --> 01:17:49.560
Right on time.

1603
01:17:51.680 --> 01:17:54.400
Is that Gideon Grey?

1604
01:17:54.640 --> 01:17:56.560
Yep. It sure is. We work with him now.

1605
01:17:56.800 --> 01:17:57.840
He's our partner.

1606
01:17:57.840 --> 01:17:58.880
And we never
would have considered it...

1607
01:17:59.040 --> 01:18:00.080
had you not opened our minds.

1608
01:18:00.080 --> 01:18:01.080
That's right.

1609
01:18:01.360 --> 01:18:02.480
I mean. Gid's turned into one of...

1610
01:18:02.640 --> 01:18:03.800
the top pastry chefs in the tri-burrows.

1611
01:18:06.480 --> 01:18:08.080
That's...

1612
01:18:08.320 --> 01:18:10.960
That's really cool. you guys.

1613
01:18:11.520 --> 01:18:12.760
Gideon Grey.

1614
01:18:13.320 --> 01:18:14.400
I'll be darned.

1615
01:18:14.600 --> 01:18:16.800
Hey. Judy. I'd just like
to say I'm sorry...

1616
01:18:17.000 --> 01:18:19.000
for the way I behaved in my youth.

1617
01:18:19.240 --> 01:18:22.440
I had a lot of self-doubt.
and it manifested itself...

1618
01:18:22.600 --> 01:18:24.640
in the form of unchecked rage
and aggression.

1619
01:18:24.920 --> 01:18:26.960
I was a major jerk.

1620
01:18:28.080 --> 01:18:31.600
Oh. I know a thing or two
about being a jerk.

1621
01:18:32.720 --> 01:18:35.280
Anyhow. I brought y'all these pies.

1622
01:18:36.680 --> 01:18:38.080
Hey. kids. don't you run through...

1623
01:18:38.200 --> 01:18:39.640
that <i>midnicampum holicithias.</i>

1624
01:18:39.800 --> 01:18:40.920
Whoa. whoa. whoa...

1625
01:18:41.080 --> 01:18:42.920
Well. now. there's a $4 word. Mr H.

1626
01:18:43.200 --> 01:18:45.760
My family always just
called them Night Howlers.

1627
01:18:47.280 --> 01:18:48.680
I'm so... What did you say?

1628
01:18:48.840 --> 01:18:49.600
Oh. Gid's talking about
those flowers. Judy.

1629
01:18:50.800 --> 01:18:52.360
I use them to keep the bugs
off the produce...

1630
01:18:52.600 --> 01:18:54.120
but I don't like the little
ones going near 'em...

1631
01:18:54.360 --> 01:18:55.640
on account of what happened
to your uncle Terry.

1632
01:18:55.920 --> 01:18:57.760
Yeah. Terry ate one whole
when we were kids...

1633
01:18:57.920 --> 01:18:59.000
and went completely nuts.

1634
01:18:59.240 --> 01:19:01.440
He bit the dickens out of your mother.

1635
01:19:01.680 --> 01:19:03.960
A bunny can go savage.

1636
01:19:04.200 --> 01:19:06.120
Savage? Well. that's a strong word.

1637
01:19:06.240 --> 01:19:07.440
But it did hurt like the devil.

1638
01:19:07.680 --> 01:19:08.680
Well. sure it did!

1639
01:19:08.680 --> 01:19:10.320
There's a sizable divot in your arm.

1640
01:19:10.320 --> 01:19:11.800
I'd call that savage.

1641
01:19:11.800 --> 01:19:15.120
Night Howlers aren't wolves.
they're flowers!

1642
01:19:15.360 --> 01:19:17.800
The flowers are making
the predators go savage!

1643
01:19:17.960 --> 01:19:19.000
That's it!

1644
01:19:19.160 --> 01:19:20.520
That's what I've been missing!

1645
01:19:21.200 --> 01:19:22.240
Oh. keys!

1646
01:19:22.240 --> 01:19:23.520
Keys. keys. keys! Hurry! Come on!

1647
01:19:23.920 --> 01:19:26.320
Oh! Thank you! I love you! Bye!

1648
01:19:31.840 --> 01:19:32.840
You catch
any of that. Bon?

1649
01:19:33.120 --> 01:19:34.200
Not one bit.

1650
01:19:34.320 --> 01:19:35.800
Oh. that makes me
feel a little bit better.

1651
01:19:36.000 --> 01:19:38.000
I thought she was talking
in tongues or something.

1652
01:19:55.280 --> 01:19:56.880
Who is it?

1653
01:19:57.320 --> 01:19:58.200
I need to find Nick.

1654
01:19:58.480 --> 01:19:59.840
Please.

1655
01:20:01.080 --> 01:20:02.160
Nick?

1656
01:20:02.880 --> 01:20:04.160
Nick!

1657
01:20:06.800 --> 01:20:08.360
Oh. Nick.

1658
01:20:08.560 --> 01:20:10.400
Night Howlers aren't wolves.

1659
01:20:10.640 --> 01:20:12.280
They're toxic flowers.

1660
01:20:12.960 --> 01:20:14.560
I think someone is targeting
predators on purpose...

1661
01:20:14.720 --> 01:20:17.080
and making them go savage!

1662
01:20:17.520 --> 01:20:18.720
Wow.

1663
01:20:19.960 --> 01:20:21.880
Isn't that interesting?

1664
01:20:24.320 --> 01:20:25.440
Wait... Wait! Listen...

1665
01:20:25.600 --> 01:20:27.040
I know you'll never forgive me!

1666
01:20:27.200 --> 01:20:28.240
And I don't blame you.

1667
01:20:29.240 --> 01:20:32.200
I wouldn't forgive me either.
I was ignorant...

1668
01:20:33.240 --> 01:20:36.880
And irresponsible and small-minded.

1669
01:20:38.400 --> 01:20:40.880
But predators shouldn't suffer
because of my mistakes.

1670
01:20:41.840 --> 01:20:43.760
I have to fix this.

1671
01:20:44.320 --> 01:20:46.600
But I can't do it without you.

1672
01:20:48.880 --> 01:20:51.640
And after we're done...

1673
01:20:51.880 --> 01:20:53.560
you can hate me.

1674
01:20:53.680 --> 01:20:56.240
And...  And that'll be fine.

1675
01:20:56.440 --> 01:20:59.640
Because I was a horrible friend...

1676
01:20:59.920 --> 01:21:01.240
and I hurt you...

1677
01:21:01.440 --> 01:21:07.920
and you can walk away knowing
that you were right all along.

1678
01:21:08.120 --> 01:21:12.040
I really am just a dumb bunny.

1679
01:21:15.960 --> 01:21:19.640
<i>I really am
just a dumb bunny.</i>

1680
01:21:21.360 --> 01:21:24.560
<i>I really am just a dumb bunny.</i>

1681
01:21:24.760 --> 01:21:27.640
Don't worry. Carrots.
I'll let you erase it...

1682
01:21:27.760 --> 01:21:28.920
in 48 hours.

1683
01:21:31.760 --> 01:21:34.240
All right. Get in here.

1684
01:21:36.160 --> 01:21:40.160
Okay. Oh. you bunnies.
You're so emotional.

1685
01:21:40.400 --> 01:21:42.720
- There we go. Deep breath.

1686
01:21:42.960 --> 01:21:44.960
Are you just trying to steal the pen?

1687
01:21:45.080 --> 01:21:46.600
Is that what this is?

1688
01:21:47.600 --> 01:21:49.440
You are standing on my tail.
though. Off. off. off. off...

1689
01:21:49.560 --> 01:21:50.520
Oh. I'm sorry.

1690
01:21:55.480 --> 01:21:58.120
Ooh. I thought you guys
only grew carrots.

1691
01:21:58.280 --> 01:22:00.000
Mmm. What's the plan?

1692
01:22:00.240 --> 01:22:01.840
We are gonna follow the Night Howlers.

1693
01:22:02.080 --> 01:22:03.280
Okay. How?

1694
01:22:03.520 --> 01:22:04.760
Know this guy?

1695
01:22:05.200 --> 01:22:07.360
Uh-huh. I told you. I know everybody.

1696
01:22:08.800 --> 01:22:11.760
Well. hello. Step right up.
Anything you need. I got it.

1697
01:22:12.160 --> 01:22:13.480
All your favourite movies!

1698
01:22:13.680 --> 01:22:16.160
I got movies that haven't
even been released yet.

1699
01:22:16.800 --> 01:22:19.800
Hey. 15% off! 20!
Make me an offer! Come on!

1700
01:22:20.080 --> 01:22:23.640
Well. well. look who it is.
The duke of bootleg.

1701
01:22:24.080 --> 01:22:25.000
What's it to you. Wilde?

1702
01:22:25.120 --> 01:22:26.480
Shouldn't you be melting down
a popsicle or something?

1703
01:22:26.720 --> 01:22:27.760
Hey. if it isn't Flopsy the Copsy.

1704
01:22:29.200 --> 01:22:31.000
We both know those
weren't mouldy onions...

1705
01:22:31.120 --> 01:22:32.320
I caught you stealing.

1706
01:22:32.440 --> 01:22:33.520
What were you gonna do with...

1707
01:22:33.720 --> 01:22:34.800
those Night Howlers. Wezzleton?

1708
01:22:34.920 --> 01:22:36.880
It's Weaselton! Duke Weaselton!

1709
01:22:37.120 --> 01:22:38.880
And I ain't talking. rabbit.

1710
01:22:39.120 --> 01:22:41.160
And there ain't nothing
you can do to make me.

1711
01:22:42.840 --> 01:22:43.800
Ice him.

1712
01:22:47.240 --> 01:22:48.320
You dirty rat!

1713
01:22:48.520 --> 01:22:49.520
Why are you helping her? She's a cop!

1714
01:22:49.760 --> 01:22:52.880
And the godmother
to my future granddaughter.

1715
01:22:53.040 --> 01:22:54.960
I'm gonna name her Judy.

1716
01:22:55.120 --> 01:22:56.480
- Oh!

1717
01:22:57.040 --> 01:22:58.200
Ice this weasel.

1718
01:22:58.400 --> 01:23:00.520
All right. all right. please!
I'll talk! I'll talk.

1719
01:23:00.720 --> 01:23:02.240
I stole them Night Howlers
so I could sell 'em.

1720
01:23:02.400 --> 01:23:04.200
They offered me what I couldn't refuse.

1721
01:23:04.320 --> 01:23:05.280
Money.

1722
01:23:05.480 --> 01:23:07.360
And to whom did you sell them?

1723
01:23:07.560 --> 01:23:08.800
A ram named Doug.

1724
01:23:08.960 --> 01:23:10.400
We got a drop spot underground.

1725
01:23:10.640 --> 01:23:11.640
<i>Just watch it.</i>

1726
01:23:11.760 --> 01:23:13.520
<i>Doug is the opposite of friendly.</i>

1727
01:23:14.640 --> 01:23:16.160
<i>He's unfriendly.</i>

1728
01:23:26.320 --> 01:23:27.720
Come on.

1729
01:23:40.480 --> 01:23:42.280
The weasel wasn't lying.

1730
01:23:42.520 --> 01:23:43.920
Yeah. looks like old Doug's cornered...

1731
01:23:44.120 --> 01:23:45.440
the market on Night Howlers.

1732
01:24:29.480 --> 01:24:31.000
You got Doug here.

1733
01:24:31.160 --> 01:24:33.120
What's the mark?

1734
01:24:33.360 --> 01:24:37.480
Cheetah in Sahara Square. Got it.

1735
01:24:37.760 --> 01:24:39.280
You serious? Yeah. I know they're fast.

1736
01:24:39.520 --> 01:24:40.640
I can hit him.

1737
01:24:40.840 --> 01:24:42.840
Listen. I hit a tiny little otter...

1738
01:24:43.000 --> 01:24:43.880
through the open window
of a moving car.

1739
01:24:58.800 --> 01:25:00.800
Yeah. I'll buzz you
when it's done.

1740
01:25:01.000 --> 01:25:02.000
Or you'll see it on the news.

1741
01:25:02.000 --> 01:25:03.480
You know. whichever comes first.

1742
01:25:04.600 --> 01:25:08.000
Hey. Doug. open up!
We've got your latte.

1743
01:25:08.160 --> 01:25:10.520
All right. Woolter and Jesse
are back. so I'm leaving now.

1744
01:25:10.760 --> 01:25:11.840
Out.

1745
01:25:11.960 --> 01:25:13.480
Hey.
Where are you going? Get back here!

1746
01:25:13.600 --> 01:25:15.520
What are you doing?
He's gonna see you!

1747
01:25:15.960 --> 01:25:17.160
- What are you looking at? Hey!

1748
01:25:17.560 --> 01:25:19.960
Whatever you're thinking.
stop thinking it. Carrots!

1749
01:25:20.960 --> 01:25:22.000
Carrots!

1750
01:25:22.400 --> 01:25:24.320
It better have
the extra foam this time.

1751
01:25:27.640 --> 01:25:28.640
Hey. open up!

1752
01:25:28.800 --> 01:25:31.000
What are you doing?
You just trapped us in here.

1753
01:25:31.240 --> 01:25:32.880
We need to get this
evidence to the ZPD!

1754
01:25:33.440 --> 01:25:35.040
Okay. Great! Here it is. Got it!

1755
01:25:35.280 --> 01:25:37.160
- No. All of it!
- Wait. what?

1756
01:25:41.000 --> 01:25:43.480
Oh. great. you're a conductor now. huh?

1757
01:25:43.600 --> 01:25:45.040
Hey. listen. It would take a miracle...

1758
01:25:45.160 --> 01:25:46.480
to get this rust-bucket going.

1759
01:25:48.440 --> 01:25:50.200
Well. Hallelujah.

1760
01:25:50.440 --> 01:25:52.800
We kinda got a situation at the lab.

1761
01:25:53.000 --> 01:25:54.520
- Oh. it just got worse!

1762
01:25:56.320 --> 01:25:57.520
Mission accomplished.

1763
01:25:57.640 --> 01:25:58.720
Would it be premature for me...

1764
01:25:58.880 --> 01:26:00.040
to do a little victory toot-toot?

1765
01:26:00.240 --> 01:26:02.720
All right. One toot-toot.

1766
01:26:05.040 --> 01:26:07.600
Well. I can cross that
off the bucket list.

1767
01:26:18.480 --> 01:26:21.000
I may have to rescind
that victory toot-toot.

1768
01:26:22.840 --> 01:26:24.240
Maybe that's just hail.

1769
01:26:24.640 --> 01:26:25.840
Come here!

1770
01:26:28.160 --> 01:26:29.280
Back off! Oh!

1771
01:26:31.120 --> 01:26:32.240
Whoa!

1772
01:26:34.360 --> 01:26:35.440
Incoming!

1773
01:26:38.120 --> 01:26:39.120
Carrots!

1774
01:26:39.320 --> 01:26:40.720
Don't stop! Keep going!

1775
01:26:40.920 --> 01:26:42.120
No. no! Please stop!

1776
01:26:42.360 --> 01:26:44.080
Do not stop this car!

1777
01:26:52.760 --> 01:26:53.760
Whoa!

1778
01:26:55.280 --> 01:26:56.320
Oh!

1779
01:27:06.480 --> 01:27:07.760
Speed up. Nick! Speed up!

1780
01:27:08.000 --> 01:27:09.280
There's another train coming!

1781
01:27:09.480 --> 01:27:11.080
Trust me. Speed up!

1782
01:27:15.200 --> 01:27:16.280
Stop the train!

1783
01:27:18.200 --> 01:27:19.200
Hey!

1784
01:27:19.360 --> 01:27:21.000
Need some help?

1785
01:27:24.480 --> 01:27:25.880
Oh. no. no. no!
Too fast! Too fast!

1786
01:27:25.880 --> 01:27:26.960
Hold on!

1787
01:27:27.240 --> 01:27:28.160
Ahh!

1788
01:27:39.360 --> 01:27:41.080
I think this is our stop!

1789
01:27:50.000 --> 01:27:52.640
Okay. maybe some
of the evidence survived.

1790
01:27:58.760 --> 01:27:59.840
Oh!

1791
01:28:02.160 --> 01:28:03.680
Everything is gone.

1792
01:28:03.960 --> 01:28:06.160
We've lost it all.

1793
01:28:06.280 --> 01:28:07.320
Yeah...

1794
01:28:07.880 --> 01:28:09.200
Oh. except for this.

1795
01:28:09.480 --> 01:28:12.120
-  Ow.
- Ooh. Nick! Yes!

1796
01:28:12.240 --> 01:28:14.360
Come on! We gotta get to the ZPD.

1797
01:28:15.080 --> 01:28:17.200
Cut through
the Natural History Museum!

1798
01:28:28.800 --> 01:28:29.920
There it is!

1799
01:28:29.920 --> 01:28:31.000
Judy!

1800
01:28:31.720 --> 01:28:33.200
Judy!

1801
01:28:33.440 --> 01:28:35.200
Mayor Bellwether!

1802
01:28:35.440 --> 01:28:36.480
We found out what's happening.

1803
01:28:36.680 --> 01:28:38.480
Someone's darting
predators with a serum.

1804
01:28:38.680 --> 01:28:40.520
That's what's making them go savage.

1805
01:28:40.760 --> 01:28:43.560
I'm so proud of you. Judy.
You did just a super job!

1806
01:28:43.840 --> 01:28:46.040
Thank you. ma'am.

1807
01:28:49.600 --> 01:28:51.400
How did you know where to find us?

1808
01:28:51.680 --> 01:28:53.360
I'll go ahead and
I'll take that case now.

1809
01:28:53.600 --> 01:28:54.880
Uh. you know what?

1810
01:28:55.000 --> 01:28:58.680
I think Nick and I will just
take this to the ZPD.

1811
01:29:03.360 --> 01:29:04.400
Run.

1812
01:29:05.600 --> 01:29:06.880
Get them.

1813
01:29:10.720 --> 01:29:11.760
Ahh!

1814
01:29:12.400 --> 01:29:13.440
Carrots!

